After reading all the pros and cons..and being one of those small guilds that must wait on the pleasure of the rot guilds, I have a equally small opinion on the matter.<br>
<br>
My opinion of no consequence is..status quo is ok. The guild leaders of the rotation guilds are nice honorable folks, and we are always patting ourselves on the back about how civilized we are to each other.<br>
<br>
I think everyone is presuming some evil intent where none was intended, or assuming some guild might decide to hold a rot on a semi permenent basis. I don't think either is true,..and from what I have heard so far we are only talking about a few weeks...not a year as implied in some posts.<br>
<br>
So unless this actually becomes a serious problem, why change the system. <br>
<br>
If it ain't broke don't fix it.<br>
